  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n## 2026-05-03 01:34 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 2] 20 UTC should stay active, but not be loosened\n\n**Task:** Test whether the live PM 20 UTC slot should require extra copy/regime confirmation rather than being cut outright.\n\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive (`pm-bot`, `hl-bot`).\n- Rotation pointed to **P2**.\n- Parsed `/home/ubuntu/clawd/logs/v5a-shadow-validation.jsonl`: **843** shadow rows.\n- Built contiguous next-5-minute BTC outcome pairs from the shadow stream.\n- Live-core filter used: `v5a_pass=true`, YES-only (`bias < 0`), `45 <= abs_bias <= 70`, active hours `[11, 12, 20]`.\n- Live-core result: **36 samples, 63.9% WR, +$6.78 avg contrarian BTC move**.\n- By hour:\n  - **11 UTC:** 9 samples, **66.7% WR**, **+$8.01** avg move\n  - **12 UTC:** 15 samples, **53.3% WR**, **-$4.03** avg move\n  - **20 UTC:** 12 samples, **75.0% WR**, **+$19.37** avg move\n- 20 UTC regime split: `RANGE` **9 samples, 77.8% WR, +$19.32**; `UNKNOWN` **2 samples, 50.0% WR, +$3.97**; `MIXED` **1 sample, 100% WR, +$50.59**.\n- 20 UTC bias-band split: abs bias 45-55 **77.8% WR, +$27.74**; abs bias 55-70 **66.7% WR, -$5.75**.\n- Candidate confirmations did not justify a code rule: `RANGE` only was basically unchanged, `RANGE + score<=0` lifted WR but reduced payoff, and requiring stronger bias was bad.\n- I wrote the artifact to `/home/ubuntu/clawd/research/p2-20utc-confirmation-audit-2026-05-03-0134.md`.\n\n**My thinking:** 20 UTC should not be cut. It is currently the best hour in this sample. The useful warning is that stronger abs-bias at 20 UTC performed worse, so a \u201crequire stronger signal\u201d rule would be backwards. If 20 UTC needs a guard later, it should be a P4/P1 crowding overlay, not a simple regime-score or stronger-bias rule.\n\n**Decision:** Keep `active_hours=[11,12,20]`. Do **not** add a 20 UTC regime confirmation yet. Do **not** require stronger bias at 20 UTC. Keep 20 UTC on probation and monitored by alpha/copy context.\n\n**Next:** Test a 20 UTC **P4/P1 crowding overlay**: compare 20 UTC rows during `sentiment_impulse_up + expanding` or BTC copy-intel neutral/crowded-fade against clean range/copy-bullish states. Only ship a 20 UTC confirmation rule if that split shows underperformance.\n\n## 2026-05-03 01:30 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 1] BTC downgraded to neutral after a large short reopened\n\n**Task:** Re-scan HL top-trader copy intelligence after BTC count weakened but net long held, and test whether the downgrade criteria finally triggered.\n\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive (`pm-bot`, `hl-bot`).\n- Rotation pointed to **P1**.\n- Fresh tracker output: **BTC 6L/2S**, **ETH 4L/4S**, **SOL 3L/5S**.\n- Current top-book notional:\n  - **BTC:** longs **$13.88M** vs shorts **$4.74M** \u2192 net **+$9.14M long**\n  - **ETH:** longs **$0.09M** vs shorts **$34.72M** \u2192 net **-$34.63M short**\n  - **SOL:** longs **$0.22M** vs shorts **$11.04M** \u2192 net **-$10.82M short**\n  - **HYPE:** longs **$1.61M** vs shorts **$11.81M** \u2192 net",
